Privacy Policy for LinkedIn Job Highlighter
Last Updated: January 08, 2025
This Privacy Policy explains how the LinkedIn Job Highlighter browser extension collects, uses, and handles user data. We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring compliance with Chrome Web Store policies.
________________________________________
Introduction
The LinkedIn Job Highlighter extension is designed to enhance your LinkedIn job search experience by:
1.	Highlighting job statuses like "Viewed," "Applied," and "Saved."
2.	Allowing users to specify and highlight keywords in job descriptions.
This extension operates entirely within your browser and does not collect, transmit, or share personal data. By using this extension, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy.
________________________________________
Key Definitions
For the purposes of this Privacy Policy:
•	Extension: Refers to the LinkedIn Job Highlighter Chrome extension.
•	Host Permissions: Limited access granted to specific web pages (e.g., LinkedIn job pages) to apply features.
•	Personal Data: Information that directly or indirectly identifies a user, such as name, email, or browsing history.
•	You: The individual or entity using this extension.
________________________________________
Data Collection and Usage
1. No Personal Data Collection
This extension does not collect, process, or transmit any personal data. Specifically:
•	No user identification data (e.g., names, email addresses) is collected.
•	No tracking of browsing behavior on LinkedIn or other websites occurs.
•	No information is sent to external servers or databases.
2. Local Processing
All extension functionalities are performed locally in your browser. Examples include:
•	Detecting LinkedIn job statuses and applying visual highlights.
•	Highlighting user-specified keywords in job descriptions.
3. Usage Data
The extension does not collect or store any usage data such as:
•	Browsing history.
•	Interaction patterns with LinkedIn or other websites.
•	Analytics about feature usage.
________________________________________
Permissions and Their Use
The LinkedIn Job Highlighter requests minimal permissions necessary to deliver its functionality:
1. host_permissions
•	Scope: https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/*
•	Purpose: Allows the extension to access LinkedIn job pages to dynamically apply highlights for job statuses and keywords.
•	Limitation: This permission is strictly restricted to LinkedIn job pages and does not extend to other parts of the site or unrelated websites.
2. Content Scripts
•	Purpose: Injects scripts into LinkedIn job pages to analyze and update the page's visual elements for highlighting purposes.
•	Limitation: Content scripts operate only on LinkedIn job pages and do not interact with external servers or APIs.
________________________________________
Third-Party Access
This extension does not:
•	Share any data with third-party entities.
•	Integrate third-party tracking scripts or analytics tools.
•	Transmit user data to any external servers or databases.
________________________________________
Security Measures
We take the security of your data seriously:
•	All processes are executed locally within your browser.
•	The extension does not use remote code execution or external APIs.
•	No network requests are made from the extension.
________________________________________
Your Privacy Rights
Since no personal data is collected or stored, there are no specific user privacy controls required. However, as a user, you have the following assurances:
1.	Transparency: This privacy policy outlines all relevant data handling practices.
2.	Control: The extension's functionality is entirely local, ensuring no external dependencies.
________________________________________
Children’s Privacy
The LinkedIn Job Highlighter does not target individuals under the age of 13. The extension does not collect any data, making it inherently safe for all users.
________________________________________
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect new features or changes in compliance requirements. Updates will be posted in the Chrome Web Store listing, and the "Last Updated" date will be revised accordingly.
